@realmoney Sep 21, 2022 | 01:00 PM EDT DOUG KASS Minding Mr. Market - Home, Home On The Range * In The Chop Bucket... As we approach the Fed's decision to raise interest rates by 75 basis points I continue to view market in The Chop Bucket - with a likely trading range of

between 3800-3850 to 4200-4250 over the remainder of the year. I have been a consistent buyer at the lower end of the forecast trading range over the last week - in the belief that we will not breach the mid-June lows. On the other hand, I respect the headwinds, especially the

rising risk free rate of return - Goodbye TINA (there is no alternative) and Hello TATA (treasuries are the alternative). I certainly am not in the "rip your face rally" camp. @tomkeene @jimcramer @ferrotv @lisaabramowicz1 @SaraEisen @carlquintanilla @ScottWapnerCNBC @business
